cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the maximum throughput of a cognitive radio user, which involves information transmission and reception. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new cooperative cognitive relaying protocol, which involves networking and communication between different users. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the system performance of a cognitive radio network, which involves control and optimization of the network. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly deal with security, but the concept of cognitive radio involves spectrum sensing and access, which can have security implications. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper does not deal with multimedia specifically, but the concept of maximum throughput can be related to multimedia applications that require high data rates.
